      • DataElement

        public DataElement(java.util.Date creationDate,
           java.lang.String name,
           ElementCategory category,
           Report report,
           boolean included,
           int position,
           DataSource dataSource,
           java.util.List<DataSourceParameterOption> selectedOptions,
           boolean fullWidth,
           boolean pageBreakAfter)
        Constructor of data element specifying all the fields
        Parameters:
        creationDate: - the date when the data element was created
        name: - the name of the data element
        category: - the category of the element
        report: - the report to which this element belongs
        included: - whether the data element is included or not in the publication of its parent Report.
        position: - the position of the data element in the report it belongs to
        dataSource: - the source of the data for this data element
        selectedOptions: - the selected options for the data source of this element
        fullWidth: - whether the element takes 2 column (full width) or only one column (half width)
        pageBreakAfter: - whether there should be a page break after the element

        Constructor of data element specifying all the fields
        Parameters:
        creationDate: - the date when the data element was created
        name: - the name of the data element
        category: - the category of the element
        report: - the report to which this element belongs
        included: - whether the data element is included or not in the publication of its parent Report.
        position: - the position of the data element in the report it belongs to
        dataSource: - the source of the data for this data element
        selectedOptions: - the selected options for the data source of this element
        displayType: - the way the data element should be displayed
        fullWidth: - whether the element takes 2 column (full width) or only one column (half width)
        pageBreakAfter: - whether there should be a page break after the element
